-- Sugar Awaiting Loading at Brazil’s Ports Fell 12% in Past Week
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-05-16T13:54:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/sugar-awaiting-loading-at-brazil-s-ports-fell-12-in-past-week.html
The amount of sugar awaiting loading
at ports in top producer  Brazil  fell 12 percent in a week,
according to Williams Servicos Maritimos Ltda.  Sugar waiting to be loaded onto ships at Recife, Maceio,
Paranagua and Santos, the country’s biggest port, totaled 1.04
million tons, figures e-mailed yesterday from the Recife,
Brazil-based shipping agency showed. That compares with about
1.18 million tons a week earlier.  Raw sugar for delivery in July fell 0.5 percent to 16.86
cents a pound by 9:33 a.m. on ICE in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
